<ol class="children">
<li class="comment byuser comment-author-mrvoid even depth-2" id="li-comment-499831">
<article id="comment-499831" class="comment-body">
<footer class="comment-meta">
<div class="comment-author vcard"><img src="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Salt-copy5.png" width="50" height="45" alt="MrVoid" class="avatar avatar-50 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-50 alignnone photo"/><span class="fn"><b>MrVoid</b> <br/><a href="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/ti-index/ti-vol-1-chapter-4-1/#comment-499831"><time datetime="2016-11-14T04:55:19+00:00"> November 14, 2016 at 4:55 am</time></a></span></div> </footer> 
<div class="comment-content">
<p>I don&#8217;t think you can make that sort of hypothesis, from a single sample of empirical evidence. Heck, we have a conflicting sample &#8212; Killing Freddy Krueger was actually the B-rank side quest, in contrast of saving anyone (I assume their main mission was to reach the town, or to just survive.)</p>
<p>If anything, you can say that b-rank side quests, have something to do with the main characters of the story, and it requires to directly affect the cast to a high degree.<br/>
In that sense, I can&#8217;t imagine what an A-Rank side quest will require of the players. If B-rank is to affect the main cast&#8230;What, A-rank is to take their place? To radically change the ending of the movie? What would S-rank be, then? Some sort of insane, over the top climax to entertain god? Blow up the planet? Become such a splendid actor, that you&#8217;re essentially The Joker in madness and scheming capabilities?</p>
</div> 
<div class="reply">
<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-login" href="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/wp-login.php?redirect_to=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wuxiaworld.com%2Fti-index%2Fti-vol-1-chapter-4-1%2F">Log in to Reply</a> <span>&darr;</span> </div> 
